SLS 26RS-127 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 6
BY SENATOR FESI
PORTS/HARBORS/TERMINALS. Expreses support for the development, construction, and
long-term operation of a liquid natural gas facility at the Greater Lafourche Port
Commission's Port Fouchon.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To express the full and unequivocal support of the Legislature of Louisiana for the
3 development, construction, and long-term operation of a liquid natural gas (LNG)
4 export facility at the Greater Lafourche Port Commission's Port Fourchon.
5 WHEREAS, Louisiana stands as the nation's preeminent hub for natural gas
6 production, petrochemical innovation, and LNG export capacity, with its coastal parishes
7 forming the backbone of America's global energy leadership; and
8 WHEREAS, through the essential operations of Port Fourchon, the leading offshore
9 energy services port in the United States, Lafourche Parish possesses unmatched industrial
10 capability, maritime infrastructure, and workforce expertise, uniquely positioning it to host
11 a major LNG export facility; and
12 WHEREAS, Argent LNG has advanced a proposal—presently undergoing the
13 Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) permitting process—for a
14 twenty-five-million-ton-per-year LNG export terminal at Port Fourchon, a project that would
15 represent one of the largest prospective private-sector investments in Louisiana in recent
16 decades and has the potential to generate billions in economic activity, thousands of
17 construction jobs, and significant long-term operational employment; and
18 WHEREAS, the project incorporates leading American industrial technologies,
